go butcher's
Homonym Number:
Word Class: phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:(elliptical for go butchers' hook, rhyming slang for look, crook) to become angry (with), go off (at); to reprimand severely, scold
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: -
Pronunciation:
Notes:
