Date:  0/0/1988
Source:  Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author:  McGILL
Vol / Page:  24
Edition:
Quote:  <i>butchers</i> to be angry, often <i>go butchers</i>; short for `butcher's hook', rhyming slang for `go crook at' - English rhyming version a `look'; eg `That teacher's always going butchers.' NZA.
